	Twitter Diaz ban     
	 London, Oct. 20 (PTI): Actress Cameron Diaz and actor Mike Myers are being banned from using Twitter as studios fear that they will unwittingly reveal secret details of their film projects.      
	According to the studio bosses, the Twitter-addicted stars are damaging the industry by leaking information on the site which has more than 2 billion followers around the globe, reports The Sun.      
	To deter actors, studios are now inserting clauses in their contracts forbidding the use of sites like Twitter.      
	Cameron Diaz and Mike Myers will star in the next instalment of the Shrek franchise for Dreamworks Studios.    
	Potter pad    
	 London: Harry Potter star Daniel Radcliffe has extended his property portfolio after buying a town house in New York worth nearly 4 million, reports The Daily Telegraph. The actor has spent 3.76 million on a building on West 12th Street.     
	Stage fright    
	 Los Angeles (PTI): Actress Scarlett Johansson may dream of making a debut on Broadway but the actress says her crippling stage fright prevents her from doing so. She says treading the boards in New York is a dream , but she has to overcome a phobia of performing live first, says Glamour magazine.                                                                                                                                                                             
